cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO

The paper proposes a method for gaze estimation using only the full face image as input, which is a problem in computer vision and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also focuses on human affect analysis, which falls under the category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The method uses a convolutional neural network, which is a common technique in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also evaluates the method on different datasets, which involves data processing and analysis, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. Finally, the method is applied to robotics, specifically for gaze estimation in robots, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics).
